Note only for make the windows binary:
Requeriments:
1) Windows OS
2) mingw32
3) qt 4.x.x

Also you can install individually minGW and qt. If you don't need the complete SDK? 
Download source packages of the Qt framework only (http://qt.nokia.com/downloads/windows-cpp)

Procedure manually:
1) Make sure you have MinGW installed.
2) Download the file qt-win-opensource-desktop-4.X.X.exe from (http://qt.nokia.com/downloads/windows-cpp)
3) Open a cmd and cd to the directory c:\qt\4.X.X
4) Run the configure program like this, configure -platform win32-g++.
5) Run mingw32-make. Note: that this step takes quite some time
6) Ensure that the MinGW bin directory and qt bin directory is in your PATH environment variable.

Automatic procedure:
1) Install qt 2010.01 (http://qt.nokia.com/downloads/sdk-windows-cpp)
2) mcos.exe for the 2010 version, Could be necesary copy mcos from the non sdk version (http://qt.nokia.com/downloads/windows-cpp)

